name: Hotel Skypark Central Myeongdong
detail: Hotel Skypark Central Myeongdong is the best hotel in Seoul because it's a new hotel with good room rate. Free in-room wifi. $10 (each trip)Limo bus #6015 to & from Incheon International airport. Do not forget to inform the 6015 bus driver to drop you in front of KEB(Korean Exchange Bank)Myeongdong, where the hotel is just located behind this building. Hotel Lotte is just situated cross the street and Myeongdong shopping is just in front of this hotel. Hotel provides maps and customer service could speak good English. Lots of good Korean Restaurants just in front of the hotel or within walking distance. Most of the scenic spots could be reached by underground train and the station entrance is in front of the hotel too. Do not forget to stay in this hotel when you travel in Seoul.

name: Hotel Skypark Kingstown Dongdaemun
detail: We will definitely stay here again when we come back to Seoul. Almost everything you need is already provided here. Free shuttle bus to Myeongdong, Seoul station, dongdaemun. Food is about 2 minutes walking distance. Free refill drinking water. Convenience store is at level 14 of the hotel. Breakfast is great (not awesome though). Ah yes, remember to go to eat at the fish street somewhere here! Small street but crowded and very delicious! Highly recommended! Adios

name: Hotel Skypark Myeongdong I
detail: I had a memorable Christmas 2018 holidays and of course, Hotel Skypark Myeongdong 1 is one of the reasons. It has been a while since I visited South Korea so I was really excited. The hotel is in the heart of Myeongdong, the shopping heaven! Really, really good location I must stay! We arrived around 5:30 AM from the airport. Check-in time was 2:00 PM (from what I remember) and we didn’t booked a room for the day before since it was a waste of money and half of the day, we will not occupy it. We regreted it though since we were so tired and we just wanted to sleep first. There were no available rooms when we arrived since it was peak season so we stayed and sleep in the sofas of the reception. Receptionist was accomodating. In the end, someone checked out early and we were able to have a room— we just paid an extra. Their room is quite small though, which I believe is normal for hotels in Seoul. Facilities is good for a small hotel. Aside from that, they have a mini restaurant too near the reception. Not that fancy but its okay. There are nearby coffee shops for your breakfast anyway. My main problem in this hotel was their WiFi. The internet was really slow. I thought South Korea has one of the fastest internet in the world, not in this location though. Also, if you are going to take Airport Limousine or train from/to hotel, with all your heavy luggages, it will be a challenge since the tiles of Myeongdong is not flat. Expect also a lot of people since the area is crowded. :)

name: Hotel Skypark Myeongdong III
detail: This is a great experience and definitely a merit in my first visit to Korea. Hotel location is just a street behind the Myeongdong main shopping area and along a main road, so you will not get disturbed by the noisy crowd, at the same time you will not be frightened by the quiet late-night street. Paris Baguette and a 7-11 is just a door access from the lobby. The Staffs are very friendly and approachable, when I request the front desk to assist me to call up a restaurant at N Seoul Tower to reserve a table for dinner, they did it immediately without a second word. The cleanliness in the hotel is also kept in a high standard, definitely comparable with a 5-star hotel. Room offered comes with a bathtub and bidet system. The room is well kept, toiletries and towels were replaced daily. This is no doubt my choice of hotel for my future visits to Seoul.

name: Bluedot Poshtel Myeongdong
detail: The staff was super friendly and made me feel right at home.

name: Nouvelle Seoul Hotel Itaewon by Aank
detail: The hotel is close to the station, 5 mins walk from there.

name: GLAD MAPO
detail: We stayed at this hotel in January, which is a very cold month in Seoul. We chose this hotel as it is just above the Mapo Station and only a few steps from the exit no. 9. Also, we went to emart via exit no. 4 for shopping before we left for airport. You can also get tax refunds on non-perishable items at emart. Coffee shops, fried chicken stalls and eating places (even Korean beef) are just opposite the road. The interior design of the room is modern with shelves, storage, hangers and beds are all very handy with a feeling of your own house. This is the best hotel I have stayed after years of travel in Korea.

name: Bobo Hotel Hongdae
detail: Modern hotel in great location for Hongdae activities. This is my fave hotel for weekend trips to Seoul to get a fix of live music (e.g., Club FF) and techno (Vurt). Plus, walking distance to great bars (Woodstack) and ethnic food (Gusto). The minimal-crisp decor (marble floor, platform cush bed) and fabulous restroom (marble/glass with best rain shower) are such a wonderful relief from the hectic Hongdae area to restore for hitting the town/nightlife. Quite, super clean/spotless, friendly staff. So worth it!

name: Riviera Hotel
detail: riviera is about 100 metres away from a subway station of line 7. the room is spacious and reasonably equipped, but with no toothbrush, shaver etc. (most of the hotels in seoul are the same). the double bed is quite large, much larger than those hotels in tokyo of similar price. staff are friendly and can communicate with simple english. haven't tried the restaurants of the hotel but there are many restaurant at the vicinity, with a 7-eleven opposite the hotel. taking into consideration the price, i.e. for five nights, riviera is a good choice, value for money.

name: NINE TREE BY PARNAS SEOUL MYEONDONG 2
detail: This is a new hotel recommended by my friend It was our wedding anniversary trip to Korea , the hotel has kindly upgraded us to a suite with the view of Seoul Tower and even wrote a congratulatory note with chocolates. This is very thoughtful The reception staff are very helpful and friendly, they can converse in English very well. The facilities of the hotel are really very thoughtful, there is lounge on the top floor to see nice view of seoul, with free coffee and water. Every floor there is ice maker machine and ironing facilities. The room I stayed are very clean and spacious (space is problem in most seoul hotel) so we choose this place due to its room spaciousness. The walk to myeongdong is about 15mins (not too far) which is perfect to be away from the noise yet convenient. The stay was perfect, i will definitely choose this place again when i go back to seoul!
